{{Nihongo|'''Keito Nakamura'''|中村 敬斗|Nakamura Keito|born 28 July 2000}} is a Japanese professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays for [[Ligue 2]] club [[Stade de Reims|Reims]] and the [[Japan national football team|Japan national team]]. He plays either as a [[winger (association football)|left winger]] or a [[forward (association football)|forward]].<ref name="Keito Nakamura Gamba Osaka Player Profile">{{cite web | url=http://www2.gamba-osaka.net/club/player2019_38.html | title=Keito Nakamura Gamba Osaka Player Profile | work=Gamba Osaka | language=Japanese | accessdate=11 March 2019 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190618061322/https://www2.gamba-osaka.net/club/player2019_38.html | archive-date=18 June 2019 | url-status=dead }}</ref><ref name="Keito Nakamura Soccerway Player Statistics">{{cite web | url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/keito-nakamura/479397/ | title=K. Nakamura | website=Soccerway | access-date=28 February 2018 | archive-date=9 May 2021 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210509181108/https://int.soccerway.com/players/keito-nakamura/479397/ | url-status=live }}</ref><ref name="Keito Nakamura J.League Player Profile">{{cite web | url=https://www.jleague.jp/en/club/gosaka/player/detail/1601793/ | title=Keito Nakamura J.League Player Profile | work=J.League English Website | accessdate=28 February 2018 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180617220043/https://www.jleague.jp/en/club/gosaka/player/detail/1601793/ | archive-date=17 June 2018 | url-status=dead}}</ref>

==Club career==

===Gamba Osaka===
Nakamura joined Gamba Osaka from [[Kantō Soccer League]] side [[Mitsubishi Yowa]] ahead of the [[2018 J1 League]] season.<ref name="Gamba Osaka News – Keito Nakamura arrival">{{cite web | url=http://www.gamba-osaka.net/news/index/no/7091/ | title=Gamba Osaka News – Keito Nakamura arrival | work=Gamba Osaka | language=Japanese | date=26 December 2017 | accessdate=28 February 2018 | archive-date=30 December 2017 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171230115125/http://www.gamba-osaka.net/news/index/no/7091/ | url-status=live }}</ref> He made his senior debut at the age of 17 on 24 February 2018 in a 3–2 home defeat by [[Nagoya Grampus]] in which replaced [[Hwang Ui-jo]] in the 69th minute and 10 minutes later crossed for [[Shun Nagasawa]] to head home and make the score 2–2.<ref name="Schedule & Results Gamba Osaka vs Nagoya Grampus">{{cite web | url=https://www.jleague.jp/en/match/j1/2018/022403/live/ | title=Schedule & Results Gamba Osaka vs Nagoya Grampus | work=J.League English Website | accessdate=28 February 2018 | archive-date=25 February 2018 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180225064805/https://www.jleague.jp/en/match/j1/2018/022403/live/ | url-status=live }}</ref><ref name="Gamba Osaka vs Nagoya Grampus 2-3">{{cite web | url=https://us.soccerway.com/matches/2018/02/24/japan/j1-league/gamba-osaka/nagoya-grampus-eight/2722181/ | title=Gamba Osaka vs Nagoya Grampus 2-3 | work=Soccerway.com | accessdate=28 February 2018 | archive-date=28 February 2018 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180228224833/https://us.soccerway.com/matches/2018/02/24/japan/j1-league/gamba-osaka/nagoya-grampus-eight/2722181/ | url-status=live }}</ref>

In total he played 17 J1 League games during his debut campaign and netted 1 goal, the winner in a 2–1 win over [[V-Varen Nagasaki]] on 24 November.<ref name="Schedule & Results Gamba Osaka vs V-Varen Nagasaki">{{cite web | url=https://www.jleague.jp/en/match/j1/2018/112406/live/#live | title=Schedule & Results Gamba Osaka vs V-Varen Nagasaki | work=J.League English Website | accessdate=1 February 2019 | archive-date=24 November 2018 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181124162538/https://www.jleague.jp/en/match/j1/2018/112406/live/#live | url-status=live }}</ref> He also scored once in 7 J.League Cup games and made one substitute appearance in the Emperor's Cup, a shock home defeat to [[Kwansei Gakuin University]].<ref name="Keito Nakamura Soccerway Player Statistics"/>

Nakamura spent a large part of the second half of the season with Gamba's Under-23 side in J3 League where he netted 4 times in 15 appearances with the goals coming against [[FC Tokyo U-23]], [[Thespakusatsu Gunma]] and [[Azul Claro Numazu]].<ref name="Keito Nakamura Soccerway Player Statistics"/>

===FC Juniors 00===
In February 2021, Nakamura has loaned to [[2. Liga (Austria)]] club [[FC Juniors OÖ]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fcjuniors.at/fc-juniors-ooe-leiht-japaner-nakamura/ |title=FC JUNIORS OÖ LEIHT JAPANER NAKAMURA |language=German |website=FC Juniors OÖ |date=8 February 2021 |access-date=9 February 2021 |archive-date=8 February 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210208161006/https://www.fcjuniors.at/fc-juniors-ooe-leiht-japaner-nakamura/ |url-status=dead }}</ref>

===LASK===
On 11 August 2021, he signed a three-year contract with Austrian club [[LASK]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[LASK]]|url=https://www.lask.at/lask-verpflichtet-linksaussen-keito-nakamura/|title=LASK SIGN LEFT WINGER KEITO NAKAMURA|date=11 August 2021}}</ref>

===Reims===
On 10 August 2023, it was announced that he would permanently transfer to Stade Reims of France's Ligue 1.<ref>{{Cite web |date=10 August 2023 |title=Keito Nakamura, l'aile gauche caviar |url=https://www.stade-de-reims.com/keito-nakamura-laile-gauche-caviar/ |website=Stade de Reims |access-date=27 September 2023 |archive-date=12 September 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230912235641/https://www.stade-de-reims.com/keito-nakamura-laile-gauche-caviar/ |url-status=live }}</ref> On 12 August, he made his Ligue 1 debut in the opening game against [[Olympique de Marseille]], coming on as a substitute in the 15th minute of the second half. On 26 September, he scored his first goal in Ligue 1 in Round 6 against [[Lille OSC]].

==International career==
Nakamura has represented Japan at Under-15, Under-16 and Under-17 level playing in both the AFC Under-16 Championship in 2016, and the [[2017 FIFA U-17 World Cup]] in which he netted 4 times in 4 games before Japan were eliminated by [[England national under-17 football team|England]] at the last-16 stage.<ref name="Keito Nakamura Gamba Osaka Player Profile"/><ref name="Keito Nakamura Soccerway Player Statistics"/>

In March 2023, he was called up by [[Hajime Moriyasu]] for the senior national team for friendlies against [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay]] and [[Colombia national football team|Colombia]]. He made his debut against Uruguay on 24 March 2023, coming off the bench in the 89th minute. The match ended in a 1–1 draw.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/report/_/gameId/665808|title=Substitute Nishimura strikes to earn Japan draw against Uruguay|access-date=24 March 2023|date=24 March 2023|author=Michael Church|publisher=ESPN|website=espn.co.uk|language=en-uk|archive-date=12 June 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230612015245/https://www.espn.co.uk/football/report/_/gameId/665808|url-status=live}}</ref> On 15 June, he came on as a substitute from the start of the second half against [[El Salvador national football team|El Salvador]] and scored his first goal for the national team.<ref>{{Cite web |date=15 June 2023 |title=vs El Salvador National Team |url=https://www.jfa.jp/eng/samuraiblue/20230615/match_page.html#pankz |website=JFA |access-date=27 September 2023 |archive-date=27 September 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230927001307/https://www.jfa.jp/eng/samuraiblue/20230615/match_page.html#pankz |url-status=live }}</ref> On 12 September, he made his first start for the national team against [[Turkey national football team|Turkey]] and scored two goals.<ref>{{Cite web |date=12 September 2023 |title=vs Türkiye National Team |url=https://www.jfa.jp/eng/samuraiblue/20230912/match_page.html#pankz |website=JFA |access-date=27 September 2023 |archive-date=15 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231115064849/https://www.jfa.jp/eng/samuraiblue/20230912/match_page.html#pankz |url-status=live }}</ref>

In January 2024, he was named for the [[2023 AFC Asian Cup]] final squads alongside Reims teammate, [[Junya Itō (footballer, born 1993)|Junya Itō]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=AFC Asian Cup 2023: Skuad Jepang Rasa Eropa, Inilah Daftar 26 Nama Pemain yang Tercatat! |trans-title=AFC Asian Cup 2023: Japanese Squad with European Flavor, Here's the List of 26 Listed Players! |url=https://www.kompasiana.com/stefanus2409/65937c70c57afb27a0177af2/afc-asian-cup-2023-skuad-jepang-rasa-eropa-inilah-daftar-26-nama-pemain-yang-tercatat |website=Kompasiana |date=2 January 2024 |language=id |access-date=5 January 2024 |archive-date=5 January 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240105094256/https://www.kompasiana.com/stefanus2409/65937c70c57afb27a0177af2/afc-asian-cup-2023-skuad-jepang-rasa-eropa-inilah-daftar-26-nama-pemain-yang-tercatat |url-status=live }}</ref>

